                     <div class="entry" id="entry-87">
                        <h3 class="entry-header"><a href="http://wallenberg.stanford.edu/blog/2009/08/article_the_new_literacy.html">Article: The New Literacy</a></h3>
                        <div class="entry-content">
                           <div class="entry-body">
                              <p>Clive Thompson on the New Literacy<br />
Wired Magazine<br />
August 24, 2009<br />
<a href=" http://www.wired.com/techbiz/people/magazine/17-09/st_thompson"><br />
http://www.wired.com/techbiz/people/magazine/17-09/st_thompson</a></p>

<p>A brief article that includes an interview with Professor Andrea Lunsford and a compelling conclusion:</p>

<p><em>We think of writing as either good or bad. What today's young people know is that knowing who you're writing for and why you're writing might be the most crucial factor of all.<br />
</em></p>
                              

                              
                           </div>
                        </div>
